The paper proposes a control formulation for flexible loads in distribution grids, which involves modeling ensembles of loads and optimizing their power consumption while accounting for network constraints. This work involves elements of control systems (cs.SY), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), machine learning (cs.LG), neural networks (cs.NE), and computational engineering (cs.CE).
